reviewText:
on the video case it said the video was made 2006, a lot has change now to 2017, like tankless hot water heaters, which we have on our 2014, that we just purchased, and a few other things that are not covered, so i guess if your motorhome is 2006 or older, it's alright.
R.W.
A must read for owners or those considering this class of motorhome. Good information and preownership consideration.
I had hoped for actual help since I cannot find a manual.  this was wasted money
